SIMPLE: globular
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Globular
<hw>Glob"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>globulaire</ets>.]</ety> <def>Globe-shaped; having the form of a
ball or sphere; spherical, or nearly so; <as>as, <ex>globular</ex>
atoms</as>.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Globular chart</b></col>, <cd>a chart of the earth's
surface constructed on the principles of the globular projection.</cd>
-- <col><b>Globular projection</b></col> <fld>(Map Projection)</fld>,
<cd>a perspective projection of the surface of a hemisphere upon a plane
parallel to the base of the hemisphere, the point of sight being taken
in the axis produced beyond the surface of the opposite hemisphere a
distance equal to the radius of the sphere into the sine of
45⟦deg⟧.</cd> -- <col><b>Globular sailing</b></col>, <cd>sailing on the
arc of a great circle, or so as to make the shortest distance between
two places; circular sailing.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Globularity</ent>⟦br⟧
